{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"21507","heading":"Implementation plan","label":"21507 Implementation plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stII/ch215","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was formerly classified to , The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.section 16935f of Title 42"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 90 days after , the Secretary of Homeland Security, the Secretary of State, and the Attorney General shall develop a process by which to implement and the provisions of .February 8, 2016section 21503(e)(5) of this titlesection 212b of title 22","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Reporting requirement","label":"b Reporting requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 90 days after , the Secretary of Homeland Security, the Secretary of State, and the Attorney General shall jointly submit a report to, and shall consult with, the appropriate congressional committees on the process developed under subsection (a), which shall include a description of the proposed process and a timeline and plan for implementation of that process, and shall identify the resources required to effectively implement that process.February 8, 2016","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"“Appropriate congressional committees” defined","label":"c “Appropriate congressional committees” defined","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Foreign Relations of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Foreign Affairs of the House of Representatives;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s21507/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs21507%2Fc%2F